# Verify build and tests after server TypeScript changes

When you change server/app TypeScript (`src/**/*.ts`, `apps/server/**`, Nest modules, DTOs, services, controllers, Prisma typings, etc.):

1. Run a TypeScript check and/or Nest build before considering the work done — prefer `npm run type-check` and, when the change affects the compiled app, `npm run build` (or the project’s equivalent)
2. Run relevant tests (`npm test`, focused Jest suites, or the closest suite that covers the touched modules)
3. **Fix compile errors** (and failing type-check) in the same change — do not leave `tsc` / Nest build red
4. Fix test failures caused by the TypeScript change in the same change when they are clear regressions
5. If a failure is environmental or pre-existing and unrelated, say so in the summary; do not ignore new compile errors introduced by your edit
6. Prefer fixing types properly (interfaces, DTO classes, Prisma types) over silencing with `any` or `@ts-ignore` unless explicitly required and documented
